text:
Forced update strikes again, bringing all 4 rooms down.  9.2/9.3 has rendered it unusable for over a week.  Bought first Sonos eight years ago quickly went to 4 rooms.  If the software and docs had been this bad then I would have taken it back.  The last straw.  

/********************/

The constant updates are a pain; particularly, since they are FORCED updates.  Really impresses people when I try to show them Sonos, and it forces me to update the controller app and multiple devices before I can do anything.  I've lost count of how many times I've just walked away (or put on vinyl... ;-)

/***Prior to 8.3***/

We have used Sonos for years.  We have it in four rooms.  However, the iOS app has gone from simple and straight-forward to incomprehensible.  In recent days, I have repeatedly been driven to my desktop out of frustration.  The iOS app is buggy.  I change rooms or queues, but they revert back.  "My Songs" is so cluttered with huge, empty place-holder icons for album graphics that it is unusable.  There is virtually no consistency between the iOS and the macOS versions.  They don't even use the same icons to represent the same features.  At this point the only room I can use Sonos without swearing is my office with my desktop.
